alternate_names: Strictly Only Brothers X Real Boi Entertainment

description.plain:
SOB x RBE consists of Yhung T.O., DaBoii, Slimmy B, Kiing Road and formerly Lul G. SOB x RBE, often called simply SOB, originate from Vallejo, CA, and have been mentored by rapper Sage the Gemini, with whom they have toured with. SOB originally stood for “sneakers over bitches”, but once the group started making music they changed it to Strictly Only Brothers. Slimmy B, DaBoii, and Lul G were all part of SOB. RBE stands for Real Boy Entertainment and was Yhung T.O.’s groups. The 2 groups combined into SOB x RBE when they were in high school and started recording music together.

The group started gaining major recognition in Northern California after they released their song “Anti”, leading to the release of their first project SOB X RBE.

In early 2018, the group released their sophomore project Gangin, and at the same time were featured on Kendrick Lamar’s Black Panther: The Album. Their song “Paramedic” off the album helped push SOB into the mainstream.

In late 2018, the group dropped their third project Gangin II.

songs.title: Paramedic!

description.plain:
Backed with hard-hitting production by DJ Dahi & CuBeatz, up and coming north-cal (much like killmonger) hip-hop collective SOB x RBE connect with fellow West Coast rapper Kendrick Lamar for an aggressive banger.

The track finds them firmly asserting with coldblooded bars that assert that they “are heavy in the streets”. Moreover, the chorus finds them “wishing a nigga would” dare disrespect them while letting everyone know that by the time they are done here, you “better call a paramedic” – even though it can’t save them.

Additionally, this is one of the more thinly veiled tie-ins to the film and the overall story of Black Panther. This song is an affirmation of Erik “Killmonger” Stevens' heritage. Hailing from Oakland, CA. The Northern California resident shows up to Wakanda with pain and fury, ready to take the throne from King T'Challa. This song is his theme.

Moreover, the title of the song is a reference to a scene in Black Panther where Killmonger pulls a heist on a museum, in which he calls for a paramedic after poisoning a museum curator.

songs.title: Anti

description.plain: Originally released as a single and taking influence from Bay Area rappers such as Vallejo rapper Mac Dre, “Anti” is SOB x RBE’s breakout song.  Featuring Slimmy B rapping the first half, and Yhung TO providing the hook and the second half, “Anti” helped solidify the group as one of the Bay Area’s top new talents.  Due to the success of the song, the group decided to compile some of their previous songs such as DaBoii’s Calvin Cambridge, and record new songs to create their self-titled album SOB x RBE.

description.plain:
Lane Changing is a song from SOB X RBE’s 2017 self-titled album, SOB X RBE. The song samples  “Ain’t Nobody” by Rufus & Chaka Khan.

On the track, the group raps about their car racing abilities and the illegal activities that they partake in as a result of their “gang” oriented lifestyles.
